Mesosoma. Mesoscutum without notaulices, dorsal surface sometimes with two irregular longitudinal rows of setae. Head width/mesoscutum width ratio 1.3. Propodeum areolated, with wide central pentagonal areola (
Fig. 7d
).

Metasoma. Petiole about 1.9 (1.7–2.1)× as long as wide at spiracles. Dorsal disc of petiole rugose, with 3–6 long setae on each side. Ovipositor sheath distinctly ploughshare shaped. Ovipositor sheath length/width ratio about 2.4 (2.3–2.5) (
Fig. 9d
).
